  "doc_id": "40009",
  "text": "In this paper we suggest an estimation procedure for sparse signals in adaptive setting based on the Distilled Sensing algorithm introduced in [CITATION_1] . In a sense, our results are optimal when the set of non-zero components of pure signal is of the order n 1−β with some β ∈ (0, 1/3). For this case we demonstrate that the asymptotic behavior of loss function is the same as for an optimal estimator up to a constant multiplier. Under general assumptions such performance cannot be achieved in non-adaptive setting. Further research could cover the cases of weaker signals when µ i are not bounded from below.",
